Senate State and Local Government 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB1675
Briggs
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1675* House Bill No. 1670
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 67-5-501(11), is amended by deleting
the following language:
"Residential property" includes all real property that is used, or held for use, for
dwelling purposes and that contains not more than one (1) rental unit.
and substituting instead:
"Residential property" includes all real property that is used, or held for use, for
dwelling purposes that can be sold and purchased as a single unit in fee simple
title, and that contains not more than one (1) rental unit.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 67-5-801(b), is amended by adding
the following as a new, appropriately designated subdivision:
(4)
(A) Notwithstanding subdivisions (b)(2)-(3), a parcel of real property containing
one (1) single family rental home or townhouse, as defined by § 68-120-101(a)(8)(C)(ii),
used, or held for use, for dwelling purposes must be classified as residential property, as
defined by § 67-5-501, regardless of whether the real property is the principal residence
of the owner.
(B) This subdivision (b)(4) does not supersede or invalidate a private agreement,
covenant, or restriction concerning the use or status of real property.
SECTION 3. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
